=Description=

Dmytri (korobokbarabok):

"I develop ZeroExchane. It's the java-based system that could help
strangers collaborate to achieve common goals by grouping in the
collective contracts and performing their obligations according this
contract.

    
Public business reputation stimulates people to be a reliable
partners. Ability of money usage allows seamlessly integrate ZE in the
existent currency systems. Each contract can be interpreted as an
'freelance'-based enterprise which allows many unfamilar people group
together to produce demanded goods and services and exchange it to
money or other goods/services. Also I plan to implement currency which
will be based on working hours, demand/supply measurement and
reputation. I think this approach will be much more better and healthy
than classical 'money has no smell' principle."


